    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix unchecked return value in lte_segmentation calls\n\n### Summary\nThe `lte_segmentation()` function can return -1 on error conditions but two call sites weren't checking the return value, potentially leading to downstream issues with invalid segmentation parameters.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/ulsch_decoding.c`: Added error checking for lte_segmentation call when computing segmentation parameters\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/dlsch_decoding.c`: Added error checking for lte_segmentation call when computing segmentation parameters\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain conditions with large transport blocks that exceed MAX_NUM_DLSCH_SEGMENTS or invalid codeword sizes, the lte_segmentation function will return -1 but the error wasn't being handled. This could lead to:\n- Invalid segmentation parameters (C, Cplus, Cminus, Kplus, Kminus, F) being used in subsequent processing\n- Potential buffer overflows or memory corruption when using these invalid parameters\n- Silent failures in the decoding process\n\nThe issue manifests as incorrect CRC calculations or memory access violations during ULSCH/DLSCH decoding when processing large transport blocks.\n"
}